.\" Manpage for BitSquat
.\" Contact: camilo.e.garcia@mail.mcgill.ca 
.TH man 7 "29 June 2017" "0.1" "BitSquat man page"
.SH NAME
BitSquat \- URL generator tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bitsquat [\fB\-n\fR \fIBITS\fR] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-f\fR \fIFILENAME\fR] [\fB\-\-available\fR] [\fB\-\-only\-ext\fR] [\fB\-\-only\-dom\fR] \fIURL\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B BitSquat
generates all possible URLs (domain name + domain extension pairs) that differ by n bits (1 by default) from an input URL.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n " " \fIBITS\fR
Set the number of bits to change.
.TP
.BR \-c " "
Only output the count of available URLs.
.TP
.BR -f " " \fIFILENAME\fR
Instead of reading from stdin read URLs to bitsquat from a file
.TP
.BR \-\-available
Only display available URLs. Determined through WHOIS servers
.TP
.BR \-\-only\-dom
Only modify domain name. Leave domain extension as is.
.TP
.BR \-\-only\-ext
Only modify extension name. Leave domain name as is.
.SH AUTHOR
Camilo Garcia La Rotta (camilo.e.garcia@mail.mcgill.ca)
